parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Tire Wear and Alignment Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature tire wear can lead to reduced traction, increased stopping distances, and a higher risk of tire failure, which can cause accidents and injuries. Alignment issues can also affect vehicle handling and stability, increasing the risk of loss of control.
Rear strut failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
